HR ANALYTICS DASHBOARD – FULL PROJECT EXPLANATION
🔹 1. Project Objective

The goal of this project is to:

Analyze employee attrition (resignations)

Understand why employees leave

Identify high-risk groups

Help HR improve retention strategies

🧾 2. DATA USED

Typical dataset includes:

Employee ID

Age

Gender

Department

Job Role

Education Field

Education Level

Attrition (Yes/No)

Job Satisfaction (1–4)

Salary / Income

Years at Company

📌 3. KPI CARDS (Top Section)
🔸 Overall Employees → 1470

Total employees in company

🔸 Attrition → 237

Employees who left

🔸 Attrition Rate → 16.12%

Formula used:

Attrition Rate = 
DIVIDE(
    COUNTROWS(FILTER(Employee, Employee[Attrition] = "Yes")),
    COUNTROWS(Employee)
)
🔸 Active Employees → 1233
Active Employees = 
COUNTROWS(Employee) - [Attrition]
🔸 Average Age → 37
Average Age = AVERAGE(Employee[Age])
